node_modules
# Keep environment variables out of version control
.env

# Tenant-uploaded assets — branding logos, attachments, etc. These are
# generated at runtime by tenant admins via /api/tenants/branding et al.
# and live on the filesystem for the lifetime of the deploy. Should
# never be in git: per-tenant PII (logos can be company-private), can be
# many MB each, and re-committing a fresh dev-DB copy keeps stomping
# over what the demo server has uploaded. See PR #938 review for the
# tenant-1/logo.png recurrence that motivated this rule.
uploads/
